<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Gender Intelligence | CMO Ladder</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@900&family=Playfair+Display:ital@1&display=swap');
        
        body { background: #050505; color: white; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
        
        .liquid-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 300px;
            height: 300px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #111;
        }

        .liquid {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 60%; /* This is our 60% Female Stat */
            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #00cbcb, #008080);
            transition: height 2s cubic-bezier(0.17, 0.67, 0.83, 0.67);
        }

        .wave {
            position: absolute;
            top: -20px;
            left: 0;
            width: 200%;
            height: 40px;
            background: url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg viewBox="0 0 100 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0 10 Q 25 20 50 10 T 100 10 V 20 H 0 Z" fill="%2300cbcb"/></svg>');
            background-size: 50% 100%;
            animation: move-wave 3s linear infinite;
        }

        @keyframes move-wave {
            0% { transform: translateX(0); }
            100% { transform: translateX(-50%); }
        }

        .stat-overlay {
            position: absolute;
            inset: 0;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            z-index: 10;
            text-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen p-10">

    <div class="max-w-4xl w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
            <div class="liquid-container mb-6">
                <div class="liquid">
                    <div class="wave"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-overlay">
                    <span class="text-6xl font-black">60.2%</span>
                    <span class="uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-xs opacity-70">Female Majority</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest opacity-30">Avg. across top 50 US Marketing Hubs</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black tracking-tighter uppercase leading-none">
                The <span class="text-[#00cbcb]">Gender</span> <br> Gravity.
            </h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-400">
                Marketing isn't just "diverse"—it is <span class="serif-italic text-white">structurally female</span>. 
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-4 border-l-2 border-[#00cbcb] pl-6 py-2">
                <p class="text-sm">
                    <strong class="text-white">The "Broken Rung" Risk:</strong> 
                    While 60% of the talent supply is female, only 93 women are promoted to manager for every 100 men in 2026.
                </p>
                <p class="text-sm italic text-gray-500">
                    "This 7% friction gap is the primary driver of the shift toward Independent and Enabled work models."
